{"actual_usd":0.16033499999999998,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":299,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31170,"reply":"\"I don't think it fizzled.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the bright square, where a bucket chain knocks once against the well-stone.* \"I think it was the actual breach.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb along the edge of the bench a second, trying to say it plain.* \"Christ rising feels less like a rehearsal and more like the king stepping back into his own house before every room's been thrown open.\"\n\n\"The thing has happened. But the whole world hasn't been brought under its full public peace yet.\" *I tilt my head a little.* \"Which is why we get this strange age where death's been dealt its mortal wound, sin's claim has been broken, the Spirit's been given—and yet people still bury their dead, still repent, still wait, still suffer.\"\n\n\"If it were a dress rehearsal, hope would be basically symbolic.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"But Christians don't mean 'spring is a nice metaphor.' We mean the tomb is empty and history has already been interrupted.\"\n\n\"So yeah—I'd say it's the actual thing, and we haven't fully caught up because the kingdom's come the way leaven comes, the way dawn comes, the way a victory gets announced in one place and then the whole countryside has to learn who's king now.\"\n\n*I look back at you, a little more intent now.* \"What part is catching at you most—the waiting itself, or the fact that the world still looks so unfinished?\"","rolling_24h_usd":92.06954999999999,"run_id":"6969274d-3304-4873-b3e3-5aa683b42f22"}
